  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Permutation in String\n\nReturn whether any permutation of `s1` appears as a contiguous substring of `s2`.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: s1 = \"ab\", s2 = \"eidbaooo\"\nOutput: true\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: s1 = \"ab\", s2 = \"eidboaoo\"\nOutput: false\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: s1 = \"adc\", s2 = \"dcda\"\nOutput: true\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Input sizes follow the original interview-style constraints.\n- Return values must match the described behavior.",
  "editorial": "Maintain only the state needed for the current window or scan. Move the left boundary when the current state violates the target condition.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nclass Solution:\n    def checkInclusion(self, s1, s2):\n        need = Counter(s1)\n        window = Counter()\n        size = len(s1)\n        for i, ch in enumerate(s2):\n            window[ch] += 1\n            if i >= size:\n                old = s2[i - size]\n                window[old] -= 1\n                if window[old] == 0:\n                    del window[old]\n            if i >= size - 1 and window == need:\n                return True\n        return False\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Ask what information changes when the right edge moves.",
    "Shrink the left edge only when the window no longer satisfies the condition."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def checkInclusion(self, s1, s2):\n        pass\n"
  },
  "entrypoint": {
